Spanish

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

Inherited from Old Spanish debuxar, from Old French deboissier.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /dibuˈxaɾ/ [d̪i.β̞uˈxaɾ]
  • Audio (Colombia):(file)
  • Rhymes: -aɾ
  • Syllabification: di‧bu‧jar

Verb

[edit]

dibujar (first-person singular present dibujo, first-person singular preterite dibujé, past participle dibujado)

  1. (transitive) to draw, to sketch
    Synonym: pintar
  2. (transitive) to describe vividly, to detail
  3. (transitive) to outline
  4. (reflexive) to be outlined, to stand out
  5. (reflexive) to be revealed, to take form
